text: Jaime Federico Said Camil Saldaña da Gama (born July 22, 1973), known professionally as Jaime Camil, is a Mexican actor, singer and television presenter. He is best known for his roles as Fernando Mendiola in La fea más bella, Rogelio de la Vega in Jane the Virgin and as Papá Enrique Rivera in Coco. ==References== ==Other websites== * Official Website * Category:1973 births Category:Living people Category:Mexican movie actors Category:Mexican television actors Category:Mexican voice actors Category:Mexican stage actors Category:Mexican television presenters Category:Mexican singers Category:Actors from Mexico City
